    "name": "Coffee Machine API",
    "description": "This collection contains endpoints for interacting with a coffee machine service.\n\n## What’s included\n\n- **Get Coffee Machine Status** (`GET /api/machine/status`): Check the machine’s current state (e.g., readiness/levels).\n    \n- **Brew Coffee** (`POST /api/machine/brew`): Start brewing coffee.\n    \n- **Fill Water** (`POST /api/machine/fill-water`): Refill the water container.\n    \n- **Fill Coffee** (`POST /api/machine/fill-coffee`): Refill coffee container.\n    \n\n## How to use\n\n1. Set the base host in your active environment (for example, `{{url}} = http://localhost`).\n    \n2. Run **Get Coffee Machine Status** first to confirm the machine is ready.\n    \n3. Use **Fill Water** / **Fill Coffee** as needed, then call **Brew Coffee**.",
