        "description": "Returns the current state of the coffee machine, including water and coffee fill levels and which drinks can currently be made.\n\n### Method & path\n\n`GET /api/machine/status`\n\n**Full URL (with base variable):** `{{url}}/api/machine/status`\n\n### Required variables\n\n- `{{url}}` — Base URL for the Coffee Machine API (for example `http://localhost`). Set this in your active environment (currently **Local**) or in collection variables.\n    \n\n### Headers\n\n- `Accept: application/json`\n    \n\n### Response (200 OK)\n\nReturns JSON with a top-level `data` object:\n\n- `data.water`\n    \n    - `current_ml` _(number)_ — Current water amount in milliliters.\n        \n    - `capacity_ml` _(number)_ — Maximum water capacity in milliliters.\n        \n    - `percentage` _(number)_ — Fill level percentage (0–100).\n        \n- `data.coffee`\n    \n    - `current_g` _(number)_ — Current coffee amount in grams.\n        \n    - `capacity_g` _(number)_ — Maximum coffee capacity in grams.\n        \n    - `percentage` _(number)_ — Fill level percentage (0–100).\n        \n- `data.can_make`\n    \n    - `espresso` _(boolean)_\n        \n    - `double_espresso` _(boolean)_\n        \n    - `ristretto` _(boolean)_\n        \n    - `americano` _(boolean)_\n        \n\n### Example response (snippet)\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"message\": \"string\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"water\": {\n      \"current_ml\": 2000,\n      \"capacity_ml\": 2000,\n      \"percentage\": 100\n    },\n    \"coffee\": {\n      \"current_g\": 492,\n      \"capacity_g\": 500,\n      \"percentage\": 98.4\n    },\n    \"can_make\": {\n      \"espresso\": true,\n      \"double_espresso\": true,\n      \"ristretto\": true,\n      \"americano\": true\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n ```"
