        "description": "Fills (adds) water into the coffee machine’s water container.\n\n**Endpoint**\n\n- **Method:** `POST`\n    \n- **URL:** `{{url}}/api/machine/fill-water`\n    \n\n---\n\n### Required variables\n\n- `{{url}}` — Base URL for the Coffee Machine API (set in the active environment, e.g. **Local**).\n    \n\n---\n\n### Headers\n\nThis request uses JSON:\n\n- `Accept: application/json`\n    \n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n    \n\n---\n\n### Request body\n\n**Content-Type:** `application/json`\n\n**JSON schema (conceptual)**\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"amount\": \"integer\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Field details**\n\n- `amount` _(integer, required)_: Amount of water to add, in milliliters (ml).\n    \n\n**Example**\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"amount\": 10\n}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n### Validation rules / constraints\n\n- `amount` must be an **integer**.\n    \n- `amount` must be **\\> 0**.\n    \n- `amount` must be **within the remaining water capacity** of the machine (i.e., it cannot overfill the water container).\n    \n\nIf validation fails, the API is expected to return a **validation error** response (see “Error cases”).\n\n---\n\n### Successful response (200)\n\nBased on the current saved/observed **200** response, the response is JSON with a human-readable `message` and a `data` object that contains an updated status snapshot.\n\n**Response shape (example)**\n\n``` json\n{\n    \"message\": \"Added 10 ml of water. ...\",\n    \"data\": {\n        \"water\": {\n            \"current_ml\": 0,\n            \"capacity_ml\": 0,\n            \"percentage\": 0\n        },\n        \"coffee\": {\n            \"current_g\": 0,\n            \"capacity_g\": 0,\n            \"percentage\": 0\n        },\n        \"can_make\": {\n            \"espresso\": true,\n            \"double_espresso\": true,\n            \"ristretto\": true,\n            \"americano\": true\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n ```\n\n**Notes**\n\n- `data.water` reflects the new water level after the fill.\n    \n- `data.can_make` indicates which drink types are currently possible given ingredient levels.\n    \n\n---\n\n### Error cases\n\n- **Validation Error**: Returned when `amount` is missing, not an integer, not greater than 0, or would exceed remaining water capacity (overfill).\n    \n\n(See the saved example **“Validation Error”** for an example payload/behavior.)"
