        "description": "Fills the coffee container in the coffee machine by adding a specified amount of coffee.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n`POST {{url}}/api/machine/fill-coffee`\n\n- Base URL is read from the active environment variable `{{url}}` (Environment: **Local**).\n    \n\n### Headers\n\n``` http\nAccept: application/json\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n ```\n\n### Request body\n\nJSON payload with a single field:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `amount` | number | yes | Amount of coffee to add **in grams**. |\n\n#### Example request\n\n``` bash\ncurl --request POST \"{{url}}/api/machine/fill-coffee\" \\\n  --header \"Accept: application/json\" \\\n  --header \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  --header \"Authorization: Bearer {{token}}\" \\\n  --data \"{\\\"amount\\\": 5}\"\n\n ```\n\n### Responses\n\n#### 200 OK — Successful Response\n\nReturns a confirmation message and the updated machine status (water/coffee levels and what drinks can be made).\n\nExample (shape):\n\n``` json\n{\n    \"message\": \"Added 5.0 g of coffee. Coffee container now has 331.0 g.\",\n    \"data\": {\n        \"water\": {\n            \"current_ml\": 902,\n            \"capacity_ml\": 2000,\n            \"percentage\": 45.1\n        },\n        \"coffee\": {\n            \"current_g\": 331,\n            \"capacity_g\": 500,\n            \"percentage\": 66.2\n        },\n        \"can_make\": {\n            \"espresso\": true,\n            \"double_espresso\": true,\n            \"ristretto\": true,\n            \"americano\": true\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n ```\n\n#### Validation Error — Validation Error\n\nIf `amount` is missing, not a number, or outside allowed limits, the API responds with a validation error.\n\nSee saved examples for concrete payloads:\n\n- **Successful Response**\n    \n- **Validation Error**"
